<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>McCoy's</strong></p><p>Part of a campaign aimed primarily at students during Fresher Week, the site was designed to reinforce McCoy's positioning as the lads' crisps.</p><p>The theme behind the site was beer trophies - those mementoes of a big night out that students seem to love.</p><p>Visitors to the site could enter their anecdotes with the best anecdotes being published and entered into a final competition.</p><p>Viral elements to support a heavy PR push included a competition to win a holiday for you and your mates.</p><p>The site was supported by PR activity in magazines such as FHM and Loaded, a DHTML banner campaign on NME, Student Brand Manager Activity and a fly poster campaign.</p><p><img alt="McCoy's website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_McCoys_a.jpg" width="280" /></p><p><img alt="McCoy's website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_McCoys_b.jpg" width="280" /></p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
